In article <16BCD13ACF.C445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu> C445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu (John Kelsey) writes:
>   I've been looking at the articles in which the PES was proposed (by
>Massey and Lai), and where the IPES was proposed (to make the PES
>more resistant to differential cryptanalysis.)  The IPES later evolved into
>IDEA.  Can anyone tell me when the decision was made to change the final
>output transformation from (MUL ADD ADD MUL) to (XOR XOR XOR XOR)?  Does
>anyone know *why* it was made?
> 

According to the papers I have, the final output transformation for IPES
(renamed IDEA) is MUL ADD ADD MUL, instead of MUL MUL ADD ADD for PES.

Bruce
